<div id="review_2122024964" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2122024964" />
    <a title="Jennie" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/69192372-jennie"><img alt="Jennie" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1499389524p2/69192372.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2122024964?book_show_action=true">Sep 15, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jennie" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jennie" href="/user/show/69192372-jennie">Jennie</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/69192372-jennie?shelf=audio">audio</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
                  <em>
                    This review has been hidden because it contains spoilers. To view it,
                    <a href="#" onclick="Effect.toggle(&#39;reviewTextContainer2122024964&#39;); return false;">click here.</a>
                  </em>
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2122024964" class="readable"
                    style="display:none"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1633902072312083159">This is my second book by Sidney Sheldon, and I was a little disappointed in this one. It seems like I was listening to a soap opera. Things just didn&apos;t seem real or believable. For instance, the two main characters continued to get burned by people after contacting people at KIG. It seems like after the first couple of times, they would realize that KIG was the common link and find another way make contact. Second, the women were shot, but didn&apos;t die because the killer wanted to have his way wi</span>
  <span id="freeText1633902072312083159" style="display:none">This is my second book by Sidney Sheldon, and I was a little disappointed in this one. It seems like I was listening to a soap opera. Things just didn't seem real or believable. For instance, the two main characters continued to get burned by people after contacting people at KIG. It seems like after the first couple of times, they would realize that KIG was the common link and find another way make contact. Second, the women were shot, but didn't die because the killer wanted to have his way with them so he used a special kind of bullet. And finally it appears that Andrew, came out of a semi vegetative state long enough to do a highly masterful deed, then slipped right back into it. It seems like Mr. Sheldon just got tired of this story all together when writing it.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1633902072312083159" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


